==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term/t|enm|soken}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|socian||to soak, steep|lit=to cause to suck (up)|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*sukōną||to soak}}, causative of {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*sūkaną||to suck}}. Cognate with {{etyl|dum|-}} {{term|soken||to cause to suck|lang=dum}}. More at {{l|en|suck}}.

